"A ueroic poem, truly such, is undoubtedly the greatest work which the soul of man is capable to perform. The design of it is to form the mind to heroic virtue by example. It is conveyed in verse, that it may delight while itinstructs : the ac- tion of it is always one, entire, and great. The least and most trivial episodes or under-actions, which are interwoven in it, are parts either neces- sary or convenient to carry on the main design; either so necessary, that without them the poem"